rape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula and mix <b>5 sec\/speed 5<b>. Mixture should be a sturdy pouring consistency; if needed, add a little extra milk and mix <b>5 sec\/speed 5<b>."},{"content":"Place a frying pan (26 cm) over medium-high heat and add a little of the extra butter. Place tablespoons of blini mixture into pan and fry for 1-2 minutes on each side, or until firm and golden brown. Transfer onto a plate to cool. Continue frying remaining blini mixture, adding a little butter to pan between batches as needed (makes approx. 36 blinis). Clean and dry mixing bowl."},{"isHeader":true,"content":"Crème fraîche with cumin"},{"content":" <strong>Insert butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Place crème fraîche, cumin, tahini and salt into mixing bowl and whip <b>10 sec\/speed 2<b>. <strong>Remove butterfly whisk<\/strong>."},{"content":"Top blinis with crème fraîche mixture and garnish with black sesame seeds and chives before serving."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Add smoked salmon and\/or caviar to blini topping.","Blinis and crème fraîche can be made up to 3 days in advance and stored in sealed containers in the refrigerator.","Garnish with thyme leaves in place of chives, if desired."],"basicInfo":["easy","45m","1h","36 portions"]}